<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,757,1573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1839" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,774,793,818]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amboinensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,774,793,818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,469,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Carcharhinus amboinensis</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 
<number box="[709,766,793,818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1839.0">1839</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was recorded in the Mediterranean on the basis of the examination of a set of jaws extracted from a large requiem shark caught off Crotone, 
<collectingCountry box="[1114,1165,829,853]" name="Italy" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Italy</collectingCountry>
(north-west Ionian Sea) (
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[158,583,865,889]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="De Maddalena, A. &amp; Della Rovere, G. (2005) First record of the pigeye shark, Carcharhinus amboinensis (Muller &amp; Henle, 1839), in the Mediterranean Sea. Annales series Historia Naturalis, 15, 209 - 212." type="journal article" year="2005">
<collectingCountry box="[158,192,865,889]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">De</collectingCountry>
Maddalena &amp; Della Rovere, 
<number box="[522,583,865,889]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The validity of the present record is questioned by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1170,1389,865,889]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article">
Bradai 
<emphasis box="[1251,1300,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1322,1381,865,889]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and by Golani (
<number box="[278,340,901,925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2010.0">2010</number>
). According to capture data in the North-eastern Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="Moreno" box="[992,1239,901,925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Moreno Garcia, J. A. (1982) &quot; Jaquetones &quot; Tiburones del genero Carcharhinus del Atlantico Nor-oriental Oriental y Mediterraneo Occidental. Ministerio de Agricultura, Pesca y Alimentacion, Madrid, 205 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Moreno Garcia, 
<number box="[1179,1239,901,925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the species may occupy a wider range than previously supposed and its finding in the western Mediterranean as Atlantic stray cannot be excluded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,757,1573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authority="Poey, 1861" authorityName="Poey" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,624,1009,1034]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longimanus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,624,1009,1034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,462,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Carcharhinus longimanus</emphasis>
(Poey, 
<number box="[558,615,1009,1034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is a doubtful species in the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Branstetter" box="[1162,1364,1009,1033]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Branstetter, S. (1984) Carcharhinidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 1. Unesco, Paris, pp. 102 - 114." type="book" year="1984">
Branstetter, 
<number box="[1304,1364,1009,1033]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); it is considered as “possible” by 
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[490,700,1045,1069]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984) FAO species catalogue. Vol. 4. Sharks of the World. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of the shark species known to date. Part 2. Carcharhiniformes. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125, pp. 251 - 655." type="journal article" year="1984">
Compagno (
<number box="[634,692,1045,1069]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but no specimens of this species are available to confirm its presence in this sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Garrick" box="[383,545,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Garrick, J. A. F. (1982) Sharks of the genus Carcharhinus. NOAA Technical Report NMFS Circular 445, 194 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Garrick, 
<number box="[485,545,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1982.0">1982</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is not included in the lists of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tortonese" box="[915,1109,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Tortonese, E. (1963) Elenco riveduto dei Leptocardi, Ciclostomi, Pesci cartlaginei ed ossei del Mare Mediterraneo. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 156 - 185." type="book chapter" year="1963">
Tortonese (
<number box="[1041,1101,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Serena" box="[1121,1279,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Serena, F. (2005) Field identification guide to sharks and rays of the Mediterranean and Black Sea. FAO Species Identification Guide for Fishery Purposes. FAO, Rome, 97 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Serena (
<number box="[1212,1271,1081,1105]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article">
Bradai 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[195,257,1117,1141]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,757,1573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authority="Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 1824" authorityName="Quoy &amp; Gaimard" authorityYear="1824" box="[151,786,1153,1178]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,786,1153,1178]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,478,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Carcharhinus melanopterus</emphasis>
(Quoy &amp; Gaimard, 
<number box="[720,777,1153,1178]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1824.0">1824</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was firstly reported on the Mediterranean coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,1154,1178]" name="Egypt" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Egypt</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tortonese" box="[187,379,1189,1213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Tortonese, E. (1951) I caratteri biologici del Mediterraneo orientale e i problemi relativi. Attualita Zoologiche, 7, 207 - 251." type="journal article" year="1951">
Tortonese (
<number box="[313,371,1189,1213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1951.0">1951</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of information received verbally from Professor Melouk of University of Cairo. 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,370,1225,1249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Ben Tuvia, A. (1966) Red Sea fishes recently found in the Mediterranean. Copeia, 254 - 275." type="book chapter">
Ben Tuvia (
<number box="[303,362,1225,1249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered Tortonese’s record to be doubtful because of possible confusion between 
<taxonomicName box="[151,303,1261,1285]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">melanopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other black-tipped sharks occurring in the Mediterranean. 
<bibRefCitation author="Quignard" box="[1084,1435,1261,1285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Capape C. (1971) Liste commentee des selaciens de Tunisie. Bulletin de la Station d'Oceanographie et de Peche de Salammbo, 2 (2), 131 - 141." type="journal article" year="1971">
Quignard and Capapé (
<number box="[1369,1427,1261,1285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
identified the species from south 
<collectingCountry box="[527,610,1297,1321]" name="Tunisia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
but no descriptive details were provided. Despite these uncertainties, the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName box="[325,517,1333,1357]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">
<emphasis box="[325,517,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. melanopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Lessepsian immigrant has been cited in 
<taxonomicName box="[1058,1123,1333,1357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sparidae" genus="Pagrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
works (
<bibRefCitation author="Branstetter" box="[1227,1431,1333,1357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Branstetter, S. (1984) Carcharhinidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 1. Unesco, Paris, pp. 102 - 114." type="book" year="1984">
Branstetter, 
<number box="[1372,1431,1333,1357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[151,350,1369,1393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984) FAO species catalogue. Vol. 4. Sharks of the World. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of the shark species known to date. Part 2. Carcharhiniformes. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125, pp. 251 - 655." type="journal article" year="1984">
Compagno, 
<number box="[290,350,1369,1393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was not included in the Lessepsian immigrant group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Quignard" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (2000) Mediterranean fish biodiversity. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 7 (3), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="2000">
Quignard and Tomasini (
<number box="[158,217,1405,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and excluded from the list of exotic species in the Mediterranean by Golani 
<emphasis box="[1090,1140,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1162,1221,1405,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) and by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Zenetos, A., Gofas, S., Verlaque, M. Cinar, M. E., Garcia Raso, J. E., et al. (2010) Alien species in the Mediterranean Sea by 2010. A contribution to the application of European Union's Strategy Framework Directive (MSFD). Part I. Spatial distribution. Mediterranean Marine Science, 11 (2), 381 - 493." type="journal article">
Zenetos 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[197,259,1441,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation box="[397,623,1441,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B., Ghorbel, M., Bouain, A., Guelorget, O. &amp; Capape, C. (2002) Observations sur les requins du golfe de Gabes (Tunisie meridionale, Mediterranee centrale). Mesogee, 60, 61 - 77." type="journal article">
Bradai 
<emphasis box="[481,532,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[556,615,1441,1465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
confirm the presence of this species in south 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1236,1441,1465]" name="Tunisia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
on the basis of a male specimen captured on 
<date box="[476,657,1477,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1993-12">
December 
<quantity box="[601,657,1477,1501]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06222" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="in" value="1993.0">1993</quantity>
</date>
in the Gulf of Gabes (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Bradai" box="[1030,1251,1477,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bradai 
<emphasis box="[1114,1167,1477,1501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[1190,1251,1477,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Doubtless this identification is correct but it is currently best to refrain from including 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1157,1513,1537]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">
<emphasis box="[971,1157,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. melanopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the official list of the Mediterranean ichthyofauna until a specimen will be available for confirmation.
</paragraph>
